1. run 'install' script.
2. open Xcode, create new project, when choosing template for your project, select 'Lightning' in left column, then choose 'Lightning App' template, JerkOff, for example.
3. select target 'JerkOff'(target name same as your project name), and add build phase 'Copy Files'. In 'Destination' drop-down list choose 'Executables', click '+' button, and select 'JerkOffBin'(or your project name with postfix 'Bin').
4. add 'Copy Bundle Resources' build phase and select needed resources.
5. run project.